Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Did I say it right?//I’m <NPCName>Wakuu</>. It’s a pleasure to meet you. Dad told me about you. He’s the one who brought you here on the chicken boat.//<portrait=happy>Yep, the one with the hat.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Did I say it right?//I’m <NPCName>Wakuu</>. It’s a pleasure to meet you. Dad told me about you. He’s the one who brought you here on the chicken boat.//<portrait=happy>Yep, the one with the hat.

Text.SourceString: Did I hear a Pokyo accent?//<portrait=normal>Oh, you are? Where in Pokyo are you from?
Text.LocalizedString: Did I hear a Pokyo accent?//<portrait=normal>Oh, you are? Where in Pokyo are you from?

Text.SourceString: Which hill?
Text.LocalizedString: Which hill?

Text.SourceString: Oh, right, the thingy… Yes, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, right, the thingy… Yes, of course.

Text.SourceString: I see… The busy part. The place with lots of cars and tall buildings, I bet.
Text.LocalizedString: I see… The busy part. The place with lots of cars and tall buildings, I bet.

Text.SourceString: Try and stay dry, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Try and stay dry, okay?

Text.SourceString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.

Text.SourceString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.

Text.SourceString: Try and stay dry, okay?//It’s stormy today.
Text.LocalizedString: Try and stay dry, okay?//It’s stormy today.

Text.SourceString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.

Text.SourceString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.

Text.SourceString: Nice weather, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Nice weather, huh?

Text.SourceString: I’m glad for this rain. The plants needed it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad for this rain. The plants needed it.

Text.SourceString: Try and stay dry, okay?//It’s snowing today.
Text.LocalizedString: Try and stay dry, okay?//It’s snowing today.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe Spring’s almost over? It really flew by, didn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe Spring’s almost over? It really flew by, didn’t it?

Text.SourceString: It’s been great spending so much time outdoors.//I like Summer too, but Spring’s my favorite season.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been great spending so much time outdoors.//I like Summer too, but Spring’s my favorite season.

Text.SourceString: Mmm, Fall. I just love the way the air smells this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: Mmm, Fall. I just love the way the air smells this time of year.

Text.SourceString: It’s crisp and kind of…spicy?//<portrait=happy>I don’t know what it is, but it makes me want to spend all day hiking in the woods.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s crisp and kind of…spicy?//<portrait=happy>I don’t know what it is, but it makes me want to spend all day hiking in the woods.

Text.SourceString: I try to visit my dad every weekend.//<portrait=normal>It might sound old-fashioned, but I kind of see it as my duty to check in on him and make sure he has what he needs.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to visit my dad every weekend.//<portrait=normal>It might sound old-fashioned, but I kind of see it as my duty to check in on him and make sure he has what he needs.

Text.SourceString: He’s getting older, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s getting older, you know.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! I’ll be at the Tavern tonight, playing pool with the gang.//<portrait=normal>You should join us!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! I’ll be at the Tavern tonight, playing pool with the gang.//<portrait=normal>You should join us!

Text.SourceString: Spring, finally! I’ve been itching to spend some nice days outdoors.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring, finally! I’ve been itching to spend some nice days outdoors.

Text.SourceString: What do you think of this weather, huh? Another gorgeous Spring day.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think of this weather, huh? Another gorgeous Spring day.

Text.SourceString: I know they’re good for me, but…green smoothies? Ugh. Can’t stand them.
Text.LocalizedString: I know they’re good for me, but…green smoothies? Ugh. Can’t stand them.

Text.SourceString: It’s always amazed me that when we look at the stars, we’re seeing light from thousands of years ago.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s always amazed me that when we look at the stars, we’re seeing light from thousands of years ago.

Text.SourceString: Some of the stars we see don’t even exist anymore!//They burned out long ago. It just took this long for the light to reach us.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the stars we see don’t even exist anymore!//They burned out long ago. It just took this long for the light to reach us.

Text.SourceString: Can’t talk right now.//I have some numbers in my head, and I don’t want to lose them!
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t talk right now.//I have some numbers in my head, and I don’t want to lose them!

Text.SourceString: How’s it going at your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s it going at your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Sure, I’d love to! Thanks for the invite.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, I’d love to! Thanks for the invite.

Special.SourceString: Great! You should stop by and see what I’m growing.
Special.LocalizedString: Great! You should stop by and see what I’m growing.

Text.SourceString: Nah, I’m sure you have it under control. You seem like someone who stays on top of things.
Text.LocalizedString: Nah, I’m sure you have it under control. You seem like someone who stays on top of things.

Special.SourceString: Okay, I guess. Sometimes I think I’m in over my head.
Special.LocalizedString: Okay, I guess. Sometimes I think I’m in over my head.

Text.SourceString: Walking to the Coffee Corner is how I make sure I get my walking in.//<portrait=normal>If I didn’t, I’d be in my office all the time… That would <Italic>not</> be good.
Text.LocalizedString: Walking to the Coffee Corner is how I make sure I get my walking in.//<portrait=normal>If I didn’t, I’d be in my office all the time… That would <Italic>not</> be good.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, even though I live right next to the hot spring, I hardly ever go there.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, even though I live right next to the hot spring, I hardly ever go there.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I’m too lazy to go grocery shopping.//<portrait=concerned>I just eat whatever we have, or I eat at the Tavern and stick the leftovers in the fridge.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I’m too lazy to go grocery shopping.//<portrait=concerned>I just eat whatever we have, or I eat at the Tavern and stick the leftovers in the fridge.

Text.SourceString: I was gardening with my dad yesterday, and his plants are looking pretty unhappy.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe you can go over there and give him some pointers.
Text.LocalizedString: I was gardening with my dad yesterday, and his plants are looking pretty unhappy.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe you can go over there and give him some pointers.

Text.SourceString: Maybe we overwatered them.//I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe we overwatered them.//I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: I’m expecting more rain in Summer.//Let’s hope my expectations are met.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m expecting more rain in Summer.//Let’s hope my expectations are met.

Text.SourceString: The lighthouse, where my dad lives, gets really stuffy when it’s this humid.//<portrait=concerned>I try to keep the door open during the day to let the air in. Not sure if it helps or not.
Text.LocalizedString: The lighthouse, where my dad lives, gets really stuffy when it’s this humid.//<portrait=concerned>I try to keep the door open during the day to let the air in. Not sure if it helps or not.

Text.SourceString: I need to make sure Dad’s heater works properly this Winter.//<portrait=concerned>I’ll order him some extra blankets too, maybe.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to make sure Dad’s heater works properly this Winter.//<portrait=concerned>I’ll order him some extra blankets too, maybe.

Text.SourceString: The neighbors usually have this big dinner party at the end of Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>I won’t be able to sleep, that’s for sure. They’ll be loud all night, so I might as well go.
Text.LocalizedString: The neighbors usually have this big dinner party at the end of Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>I won’t be able to sleep, that’s for sure. They’ll be loud all night, so I might as well go.

Text.SourceString: Cleaning all the dead leaves off the telescope is such a pain.
Text.LocalizedString: Cleaning all the dead leaves off the telescope is such a pain.

Text.SourceString: I live at the observatory with my housemate, <NPCName>Chaem</>. Feel free to stop by any time!
Text.LocalizedString: I live at the observatory with my housemate, <NPCName>Chaem</>. Feel free to stop by any time!

Text.SourceString: You don’t know where it is?//It’s right behind the vineyard.//Do you know where the vineyard is?
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t know where it is?//It’s right behind the vineyard.//Do you know where the vineyard is?

Text.SourceString: Brrrr. My toes are going numb!
Text.LocalizedString: Brrrr. My toes are going numb!

Text.SourceString: Seems like it’s been snowing for days…
Text.LocalizedString: Seems like it’s been snowing for days…

Text.SourceString: This storm is intense! The wind must be blowing fifty miles an hour.
Text.LocalizedString: This storm is intense! The wind must be blowing fifty miles an hour.

Text.SourceString: Stay safe, okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Watch out for flying objects.
Text.LocalizedString: Stay safe, okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Watch out for flying objects.

Text.SourceString: Gah! I <Italic>need</> to go to the Coffee Corner in front of Fishensips tomorrow.//<portrait=normal>The coffee is great, and nothing compares to their muffins!
Text.LocalizedString: Gah! I <Italic>need</> to go to the Coffee Corner in front of Fishensips tomorrow.//<portrait=normal>The coffee is great, and nothing compares to their muffins!

Text.SourceString: I'm pretty sure <NpcName>Raj</> gets the coffee beans locally, but I can't say for sure.//If you're curious, just ask them! I don't think they'd mind sharing that info.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm pretty sure <NpcName>Raj</> gets the coffee beans locally, but I can't say for sure.//If you're curious, just ask them! I don't think they'd mind sharing that info.

Text.SourceString: One reason why traveling is cool is that the constellations look different depending on where you are!//<portrait=happy>Isn’t that wild?
Text.LocalizedString: One reason why traveling is cool is that the constellations look different depending on where you are!//<portrait=happy>Isn’t that wild?

Text.SourceString: I’ve cut back on eating fish, but I’ve gotta admit, I still love me some salmon.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve cut back on eating fish, but I’ve gotta admit, I still love me some salmon.

Text.SourceString: Know what I could go for right now? A vegan taco.
Text.LocalizedString: Know what I could go for right now? A vegan taco.

Text.SourceString: Ever tried cenil? It’s so good!//I’ve been a fan since I was a kid.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever tried cenil? It’s so good!//I’ve been a fan since I was a kid.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to send you some cenil sometime. I hope that’s okay with you.//<portrait=happy>Don’t worry, it won’t be my cooking, so you can feast without fear! Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to send you some cenil sometime. I hope that’s okay with you.//<portrait=happy>Don’t worry, it won’t be my cooking, so you can feast without fear! Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: I’ve tried so many fruits in my life, but mangoes will always be my number one favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve tried so many fruits in my life, but mangoes will always be my number one favorite.

Text.SourceString: The cold is making me crave chocolate chip muffins.//Do you want some too?
Text.LocalizedString: The cold is making me crave chocolate chip muffins.//Do you want some too?

Text.SourceString: I grew up on my dad’s fishing boat, the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. It was a pretty unique childhood, let me tell you!
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up on my dad’s fishing boat, the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. It was a pretty unique childhood, let me tell you!

Text.SourceString: I mean, it’s the only childhood I had, so it felt normal to me.//<portrait=normal>But I was always jealous of other kids who went to school and played sports…all that regular stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, it’s the only childhood I had, so it felt normal to me.//<portrait=normal>But I was always jealous of other kids who went to school and played sports…all that regular stuff.

Text.SourceString: That’s why going to college was so important to me.//<portrait=happy>To reclaim some of that normalcy. You know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: That’s why going to college was so important to me.//<portrait=happy>To reclaim some of that normalcy. You know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: I tried to get in some stargazing last night, but it was too cloudy. Disappointing.//<portrait=normal>The Winter sky, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to get in some stargazing last night, but it was too cloudy. Disappointing.//<portrait=normal>The Winter sky, huh?

Text.SourceString: Can’t talk right now. I have some numbers in my head, and I don’t want to lose them!//Gotta run to my computer and do some calculations.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t talk right now. I have some numbers in my head, and I don’t want to lose them!//Gotta run to my computer and do some calculations.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Chaem</>? I’m not sure where she is. Why?//<portrait=annoyed>You should try the beach. She might be there practicing.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Chaem</>? I’m not sure where she is. Why?//<portrait=annoyed>You should try the beach. She might be there practicing.

Text.SourceString: It’s really beautiful this time of year. Peaceful too.//<portrait=happy>Spring is truly special here.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s really beautiful this time of year. Peaceful too.//<portrait=happy>Spring is truly special here.

Text.SourceString: Can you tell the difference between a star and a planet when you look at the night sky?//I guess it takes some practice.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you tell the difference between a star and a planet when you look at the night sky?//I guess it takes some practice.

Text.SourceString: For one thing, stars are like dots, but planets are more spherical.//Stars cast their own light, like our sun, but planets reflect light. Also, stars twinkle. Planets don’t.//<portrait=happy>Sorry I got carried away talking about stars. I hope I didn’t bore you.
Text.LocalizedString: For one thing, stars are like dots, but planets are more spherical.//Stars cast their own light, like our sun, but planets reflect light. Also, stars twinkle. Planets don’t.//<portrait=happy>Sorry I got carried away talking about stars. I hope I didn’t bore you.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Are you going to the Cherry Blossom Festival?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Are you going to the Cherry Blossom Festival?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been trying to get my dad to come, but he doesn’t want to.//<portrait=sad>Maybe you can help me convince him.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been trying to get my dad to come, but he doesn’t want to.//<portrait=sad>Maybe you can help me convince him.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I miss the Summer sunsets on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. We had a panoramic view.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I miss the Summer sunsets on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. We had a panoramic view.

Text.SourceString: Summer days like these remind me of my childhood.//Dad and I used to spend nights looking at the stars on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer days like these remind me of my childhood.//Dad and I used to spend nights looking at the stars on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>.

Text.SourceString: Some of my most memorable Summers were spent at sea, I have to admit.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my most memorable Summers were spent at sea, I have to admit.

Text.SourceString: Growing up on a boat was tough. I didn’t have any friends my own age.//It might have stunted my social development.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up on a boat was tough. I didn’t have any friends my own age.//It might have stunted my social development.

Text.SourceString: Thanks, <PlayerName>$player</>. I always feel comfortable talking to you.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks, <PlayerName>$player</>. I always feel comfortable talking to you.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha, see? I say awkward things, and then the conversation just sort of…
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha, see? I say awkward things, and then the conversation just sort of…

Text.SourceString: Well… The more we know about each other, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Well… The more we know about each other, right?

Text.SourceString: One nice thing about being an astronomer is you can do it anywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: One nice thing about being an astronomer is you can do it anywhere.

Text.SourceString: If I’d become a fisher like my dad wanted, I’d have to be out at sea. But an astronomer has more freedom. There are stars wherever you go.
Text.LocalizedString: If I’d become a fisher like my dad wanted, I’d have to be out at sea. But an astronomer has more freedom. There are stars wherever you go.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been thinking about where else I might live if my dad weren’t here.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been thinking about where else I might live if my dad weren’t here.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell him I said that, though.//<portrait=sad>I don’t want him to know I’ve been thinking about it. He’d take it wrong.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell him I said that, though.//<portrait=sad>I don’t want him to know I’ve been thinking about it. He’d take it wrong.

Text.SourceString: I learned how to play pool when I was young.//Some of the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>’s crew taught me when we were in port.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned how to play pool when I was young.//Some of the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>’s crew taught me when we were in port.

Text.SourceString: I guess they shouldn’t have been taking me into taverns at such a young age.//<portrait=normal>But no one ever stopped us!
Text.LocalizedString: I guess they shouldn’t have been taking me into taverns at such a young age.//<portrait=normal>But no one ever stopped us!

Text.SourceString: There are so many dead leaves everywhere now. I hope they don’t get stuck in our drain.//That’d be a nightmare to clean.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many dead leaves everywhere now. I hope they don’t get stuck in our drain.//That’d be a nightmare to clean.

Text.SourceString: The beach cleanup last week was a win, wasn’t it? A lot of people came to help.//<portrait=normal>It was really hot, but it was worth it. We did good!
Text.LocalizedString: The beach cleanup last week was a win, wasn’t it? A lot of people came to help.//<portrait=normal>It was really hot, but it was worth it. We did good!

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Takeba</> talking to some guy yesterday, mistaking him for his son again.//<portrait=sad>Poor man must really miss his son.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Takeba</> talking to some guy yesterday, mistaking him for his son again.//<portrait=sad>Poor man must really miss his son.

Text.SourceString: Does this hair color suit me, you think? I might dye it a different color, if not.//But I have to leave it a couple weeks. Might have to wait till Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Does this hair color suit me, you think? I might dye it a different color, if not.//But I have to leave it a couple weeks. Might have to wait till Winter.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Erika</> said the color is fitting for the “crispy season” now. I assumed she meant Fall.//<portrait=normal>I don’t really care about my hair fitting the season. Does it fit <Italic>my face</>?//Also, why is Fall “crispy”?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Erika</> said the color is fitting for the “crispy season” now. I assumed she meant Fall.//<portrait=normal>I don’t really care about my hair fitting the season. Does it fit <Italic>my face</>?//Also, why is Fall “crispy”?

Text.SourceString: I like your Fall outfit.//It looks nice.
Text.LocalizedString: I like your Fall outfit.//It looks nice.

Text.SourceString: I had some pumpkin pie earlier today. The neighbor baked one too many and sent us some.//It was good, yeah. Nothing special, but yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: I had some pumpkin pie earlier today. The neighbor baked one too many and sent us some.//It was good, yeah. Nothing special, but yeah.

Text.SourceString: I walked past the cemetery last week, and it was mossy! Dead leaves everywhere. But then it was all nice and clean yesterday.//I think the <NpcName>Sanchez</> brothers are working extra hard cleaning it up this Fall. Good men.
Text.LocalizedString: I walked past the cemetery last week, and it was mossy! Dead leaves everywhere. But then it was all nice and clean yesterday.//I think the <NpcName>Sanchez</> brothers are working extra hard cleaning it up this Fall. Good men.

Text.SourceString: Gloves aren’t for me. They feel weird on my hands. Hate the way they feel.//<portrait=annoyed>Not just that. They make my hands even colder. How is that possible?
Text.LocalizedString: Gloves aren’t for me. They feel weird on my hands. Hate the way they feel.//<portrait=annoyed>Not just that. They make my hands even colder. How is that possible?

Text.SourceString: Accidentally stepped in a puddle when I went outside with no shoes this morning.//<portrait=concerned>And now I can’t feel the toes on my right foot. Dang it!
Text.LocalizedString: Accidentally stepped in a puddle when I went outside with no shoes this morning.//<portrait=concerned>And now I can’t feel the toes on my right foot. Dang it!

Text.SourceString: Gah! I’ll be sure to always wear shoes from now on.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah! I’ll be sure to always wear shoes from now on.

Text.SourceString: Enjoying the snow?
Text.LocalizedString: Enjoying the snow?

Text.SourceString: The observatory can get cold. For one, the building is huge, and the ceiling is <Italic>really</> high.//The heater has to work <Italic>overtime</> to keep all that space warm.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s a waste of money to run the heat in the main area, so we usually only have it on in the bedrooms.
Text.LocalizedString: The observatory can get cold. For one, the building is huge, and the ceiling is <Italic>really</> high.//The heater has to work <Italic>overtime</> to keep all that space warm.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s a waste of money to run the heat in the main area, so we usually only have it on in the bedrooms.

Text.SourceString: How do you keep moisturized in the dry Winter weather?//<portrait=annoyed>I’m drinking extra water, but it but it doesn’t seem to help. My hands feel like they’re made of ceramic that’s about to crack.
Text.LocalizedString: How do you keep moisturized in the dry Winter weather?//<portrait=annoyed>I’m drinking extra water, but it but it doesn’t seem to help. My hands feel like they’re made of ceramic that’s about to crack.

Text.SourceString: Maybe it’s not the dryness, could be the dish soap. We bought the cheapest one.//<portrait=annoyed>I’ll start wearing gloves when I do dishes. That should help.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe it’s not the dryness, could be the dish soap. We bought the cheapest one.//<portrait=annoyed>I’ll start wearing gloves when I do dishes. That should help.

Text.SourceString: I think bamboo shoots only grow during Spring, which means we’ve got less than a week to gather them.
Text.LocalizedString: I think bamboo shoots only grow during Spring, which means we’ve got less than a week to gather them.

Text.SourceString: If I remember correctly, my dad once mentioned you can only find bamboo shoots in the bamboo forest.//It’s right behind the observatory and around the hot spring.
Text.LocalizedString: If I remember correctly, my dad once mentioned you can only find bamboo shoots in the bamboo forest.//It’s right behind the observatory and around the hot spring.

Text.SourceString: And since bamboo shoots only grow during Spring, that makes them a rare find, doesn’t it?//<portrait=happy>All right, don’t quote me on the “only grow during Spring” bit. I’m not sure about that one.
Text.LocalizedString: And since bamboo shoots only grow during Spring, that makes them a rare find, doesn’t it?//<portrait=happy>All right, don’t quote me on the “only grow during Spring” bit. I’m not sure about that one.

Text.SourceString: [You wonder what song he’s humming. It’s upbeat.]//I love Spring days like this!
Text.LocalizedString: [You wonder what song he’s humming. It’s upbeat.]//I love Spring days like this!

Text.SourceString: I should go to <NpcName>Sam’s</> and get some seeds for the lighthouse patch. We’re running out.
Text.LocalizedString: I should go to <NpcName>Sam’s</> and get some seeds for the lighthouse patch. We’re running out.

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking of buying radish seeds…or maybe strawberries. What’s better? They’re Spring seeds, aren’t they?//Which one do you think my dad would like?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking of buying radish seeds…or maybe strawberries. What’s better? They’re Spring seeds, aren’t they?//Which one do you think my dad would like?

Text.SourceString: If I’m right, wasabi only grows during Spring, which means we have less than two weeks to gather it.
Text.LocalizedString: If I’m right, wasabi only grows during Spring, which means we have less than two weeks to gather it.

Text.SourceString: Wasabi’s all right. It’s a handy condiment for stargazing. Keeps you awake.//Nothing special.
Text.LocalizedString: Wasabi’s all right. It’s a handy condiment for stargazing. Keeps you awake.//Nothing special.

Text.SourceString: I’d totally camp out more often if it weren’t for all those giant mosquitos.//<portrait=annoyed>But hey, I do live in the middle of the forest, so I guess I can’t really blame them when I’m the one crashing their party.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d totally camp out more often if it weren’t for all those giant mosquitos.//<portrait=annoyed>But hey, I do live in the middle of the forest, so I guess I can’t really blame them when I’m the one crashing their party.

Text.SourceString: Plus, it’s Summer right now, which is basically bug season.
Text.LocalizedString: Plus, it’s Summer right now, which is basically bug season.

Text.SourceString: Is it corn season yet? Do you grow it on your farm?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it corn season yet? Do you grow it on your farm?

Text.SourceString: The Beach Cleanup Festival is important to our community.//It’s a great tradition, and I’m glad we’re keeping it going.
Text.LocalizedString: The Beach Cleanup Festival is important to our community.//It’s a great tradition, and I’m glad we’re keeping it going.

Text.SourceString: The next one’s happening on the 27th.//<portrait=annoyed>Just come to the beach whenever you’re ready, and you’ll see a bunch of people setting up water booths and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: The next one’s happening on the 27th.//<portrait=annoyed>Just come to the beach whenever you’re ready, and you’ll see a bunch of people setting up water booths and stuff.

Text.SourceString: Pulling up trash when you’re fishing isn’t a waste. That’s one less piece of garbage in the water for fish to eat.//It really does make a difference.
Text.LocalizedString: Pulling up trash when you’re fishing isn’t a waste. That’s one less piece of garbage in the water for fish to eat.//It really does make a difference.

Text.SourceString: One of the good things about living at the observatory is you can hear the bugs singing on Summer nights.
Text.LocalizedString: One of the good things about living at the observatory is you can hear the bugs singing on Summer nights.

Text.SourceString: This wind is intense! If it were a little stronger, I think it’d be a storm.
Text.LocalizedString: This wind is intense! If it were a little stronger, I think it’d be a storm.

Text.SourceString: It’s snowing, isn’t it? You have snow on your nose.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s snowing, isn’t it? You have snow on your nose.

Text.SourceString: Being out in the snow isn’t too bad.//It’s cold, but it’s not as cold as I thought it would be.
Text.LocalizedString: Being out in the snow isn’t too bad.//It’s cold, but it’s not as cold as I thought it would be.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Chaem</> was going around covered in snow this morning. Boggles my mind why she doesn’t brush it off.//She likes it, I guess. Maybe it’s good for her training or something like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Chaem</> was going around covered in snow this morning. Boggles my mind why she doesn’t brush it off.//She likes it, I guess. Maybe it’s good for her training or something like that.

Text.SourceString: I’m nervous about seeing my dad this weekend.//I just know he’s gonna find something to criticize.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m nervous about seeing my dad this weekend.//I just know he’s gonna find something to criticize.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know what it’s gonna be, but I can feel it coming.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know what it’s gonna be, but I can feel it coming.

Text.SourceString: Dad’s not too thrilled about the moss on the lighthouse. He’s afraid it’s after his plants.//No matter how much we try to remove it, it keeps coming back. It’s moss, for crying out loud!
Text.LocalizedString: Dad’s not too thrilled about the moss on the lighthouse. He’s afraid it’s after his plants.//No matter how much we try to remove it, it keeps coming back. It’s moss, for crying out loud!

Text.SourceString: Even with all the moss, I think the lighthouse is in great shape. It’s an old building. But that doesn’t matter.//<Italic>Nothing</> will ever be good enough for him.
Text.LocalizedString: Even with all the moss, I think the lighthouse is in great shape. It’s an old building. But that doesn’t matter.//<Italic>Nothing</> will ever be good enough for him.

Text.SourceString: Living in an inn like <NpcName>Raj</> sounds kinda nice, especially during these crazy snowstorms.//They said the heater works <Italic>most</> of the time, and if not, the twins make sure everyone has extra blankets.
Text.LocalizedString: Living in an inn like <NpcName>Raj</> sounds kinda nice, especially during these crazy snowstorms.//They said the heater works <Italic>most</> of the time, and if not, the twins make sure everyone has extra blankets.

Text.SourceString: They said it’s worth every penny!
Text.LocalizedString: They said it’s worth every penny!

Text.SourceString: I chatted with <NpcName>Aaliyah</> once, and she’s gotta be one of the smartest people I’ve ever met.//<portrait=normal>It must take a lot of work to be that knowledgeable and accomplished.
Text.LocalizedString: I chatted with <NpcName>Aaliyah</> once, and she’s gotta be one of the smartest people I’ve ever met.//<portrait=normal>It must take a lot of work to be that knowledgeable and accomplished.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I wish I had my dad’s skills, like his green thumb or fishing instincts.//<portrait=sad>He’s just so in tune with nature, and I feel like I’m nowhere close to that.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I wish I had my dad’s skills, like his green thumb or fishing instincts.//<portrait=sad>He’s just so in tune with nature, and I feel like I’m nowhere close to that.

Text.SourceString: You’re a good person, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad you moved here.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a good person, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad you moved here.

Text.SourceString: I like being out in nature. Growing up on a boat probably had something to do with it.//When I’m indoors, I feel like the walls are squeezing in on me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like being out in nature. Growing up on a boat probably had something to do with it.//When I’m indoors, I feel like the walls are squeezing in on me.

Text.SourceString: Of course, work sometimes requires me to be inside.//But my favorite workdays – or work nights, rather – are the ones I spend outside, studying the universe.
Text.LocalizedString: Of course, work sometimes requires me to be inside.//But my favorite workdays – or work nights, rather – are the ones I spend outside, studying the universe.

Text.SourceString: When I told my dad I wanted to go to college and become an astronomer… Let’s just say he wasn’t pleased.//<portrait=annoyed>That’s an understatement, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: When I told my dad I wanted to go to college and become an astronomer… Let’s just say he wasn’t pleased.//<portrait=annoyed>That’s an understatement, actually.

Text.SourceString: He took it personally. It didn’t matter how much I tried to explain I really love astronomy.//<portrait=concerned>What I wanted didn’t seem to matter to him.
Text.LocalizedString: He took it personally. It didn’t matter how much I tried to explain I really love astronomy.//<portrait=concerned>What I wanted didn’t seem to matter to him.

Text.SourceString: I was always the good kid, growing up. I didn’t want to let my dad down.//<portrait=sad>When you disappoint him, he lets you know it!
Text.LocalizedString: I was always the good kid, growing up. I didn’t want to let my dad down.//<portrait=sad>When you disappoint him, he lets you know it!

Text.SourceString: I went a little crazy in college. I guess I was rebelling. But I think I’ve settled into a decent person.
Text.LocalizedString: I went a little crazy in college. I guess I was rebelling. But I think I’ve settled into a decent person.

Text.SourceString: When I was a kid on the boat, I’d go on deck at night and lie there and just look up at the stars.//<portrait=normal>I want to know what’s out there.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was a kid on the boat, I’d go on deck at night and lie there and just look up at the stars.//<portrait=normal>I want to know what’s out there.

Text.SourceString: I think my dad feels the same way about the sea.//He wants to keep sailing until he reaches the end of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I think my dad feels the same way about the sea.//He wants to keep sailing until he reaches the end of it.

Text.SourceString: We’re more similar than he thinks. I just wish he could see that.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re more similar than he thinks. I just wish he could see that.

Text.SourceString: Rainy days like this are a good time to get work done and catch up on my reading, but I just hate being cooped up indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: Rainy days like this are a good time to get work done and catch up on my reading, but I just hate being cooped up indoors.

Text.SourceString: Then again… If you’re cooped up indoors with me, maybe it won’t be so bad…
Text.LocalizedString: Then again… If you’re cooped up indoors with me, maybe it won’t be so bad…

Text.SourceString: Now it’s Spring, I guess you’ll be busier on the farm.//<portrait=concerned>I hope it doesn’t mean we won’t see each other as much.
Text.LocalizedString: Now it’s Spring, I guess you’ll be busier on the farm.//<portrait=concerned>I hope it doesn’t mean we won’t see each other as much.

Text.SourceString: Grab a drink with me at the Tavern tonight, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Grab a drink with me at the Tavern tonight, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been reading up on black holes to prepare for my presentation, and I’m getting excited about them all over again!//<portrait=happy>For example, did you know there’s a supermassive black hole at the core of our galaxy? It’s dormant now, but it was probably much more active a few million years ago.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been reading up on black holes to prepare for my presentation, and I’m getting excited about them all over again!//<portrait=happy>For example, did you know there’s a supermassive black hole at the core of our galaxy? It’s dormant now, but it was probably much more active a few million years ago.

Text.SourceString: It’s more than fourteen million miles wide. That’s around seventeen times the size of the sun! How did that black hole get there? How did it get so big?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s more than fourteen million miles wide. That’s around seventeen times the size of the sun! How did that black hole get there? How did it get so big?

Text.SourceString: My dad and I haven’t been getting along so well lately.//<portrait=concerned>He just can’t understand why I wanted to go into astronomy rather than taking over for him on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>.
Text.LocalizedString: My dad and I haven’t been getting along so well lately.//<portrait=concerned>He just can’t understand why I wanted to go into astronomy rather than taking over for him on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>.

Text.SourceString: And the problem is he won’t keep his opinions to himself.
Text.LocalizedString: And the problem is he won’t keep his opinions to himself.

Text.SourceString: You might be wondering about <NPCName>Chaem</> and me.//We live together, but we’re just friends. Strictly platonic.
Text.LocalizedString: You might be wondering about <NPCName>Chaem</> and me.//We live together, but we’re just friends. Strictly platonic.

Text.SourceString: Um… You know. Just in case you thought…well…never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Um… You know. Just in case you thought…well…never mind.

Text.SourceString: Looking back, I realize I had a pretty conservative upbringing.//Not that I knew it at the time, since I didn’t have anything to compare it to.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking back, I realize I had a pretty conservative upbringing.//Not that I knew it at the time, since I didn’t have anything to compare it to.

Text.SourceString: But now I can see that I didn’t have a lot of time to just be a kid.//If I ever have kids of my own, I want their experience to be different.//<portrait=blushing>I want them to have the freedom to explore and enjoy the world around them and to have plenty of opportunities to just be kids.
Text.LocalizedString: But now I can see that I didn’t have a lot of time to just be a kid.//If I ever have kids of my own, I want their experience to be different.//<portrait=blushing>I want them to have the freedom to explore and enjoy the world around them and to have plenty of opportunities to just be kids.

Text.SourceString: I always enjoy talking to you.
Text.LocalizedString: I always enjoy talking to you.

Text.SourceString: I find myself thinking about you quite often. You have an unforgettable presence.
Text.LocalizedString: I find myself thinking about you quite often. You have an unforgettable presence.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mean to be forward, but you have a certain something that makes me want to get to know you better.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mean to be forward, but you have a certain something that makes me want to get to know you better.

Text.SourceString: You look incredible today.//I’m speechless.
Text.LocalizedString: You look incredible today.//I’m speechless.

Text.SourceString: Your eyes are absolutely stunning. I can’t help but get lost in them.
Text.LocalizedString: Your eyes are absolutely stunning. I can’t help but get lost in them.

Text.SourceString: You have a captivating smile.//It brightens up my day every time I see it.
Text.LocalizedString: You have a captivating smile.//It brightens up my day every time I see it.

Text.SourceString: You look cold, <PlayerName>$player</>! But not in a bad way.//You’re kind of cute with red cheeks.
Text.LocalizedString: You look cold, <PlayerName>$player</>! But not in a bad way.//You’re kind of cute with red cheeks.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to New Year’s. It feels good to start over with a clean slate.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to New Year’s. It feels good to start over with a clean slate.

Text.SourceString: I grew up without a mother, so Dad is the only family I have.//<portrait=concerned>It’s tough that we don’t always get along, because without him, I’d be completely alone.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up without a mother, so Dad is the only family I have.//<portrait=concerned>It’s tough that we don’t always get along, because without him, I’d be completely alone.

Text.SourceString: As he’s getting older, I feel like it’s becoming more important than ever for us to have a good relationship, but at the same time, it’s becoming harder and <Italic>harder</> to achieve.
Text.LocalizedString: As he’s getting older, I feel like it’s becoming more important than ever for us to have a good relationship, but at the same time, it’s becoming harder and <Italic>harder</> to achieve.

Text.SourceString: Did you know if you discover a star, you get to give it a name?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know if you discover a star, you get to give it a name?

Text.SourceString: I guess so, yeah. Though it doesn’t seem as exciting as getting to name a star after yourself.//<portrait=happy>Personally, I’d rather have a star named after me than a disease.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess so, yeah. Though it doesn’t seem as exciting as getting to name a star after yourself.//<portrait=happy>Personally, I’d rather have a star named after me than a disease.

Special.SourceString: Kind of like with a disease.
Special.LocalizedString: Kind of like with a disease.

Text.SourceString: You think so? Whoa! That’s one heck of a compliment.
Text.LocalizedString: You think so? Whoa! That’s one heck of a compliment.

Special.SourceString: I could see a star named Wakuu.
Special.LocalizedString: I could see a star named Wakuu.

Text.SourceString: Oops! Sorry about that. I didn’t mean to.
Text.LocalizedString: Oops! Sorry about that. I didn’t mean to.

Text.SourceString: Next week is already Fall. I might need to change my hair color to match the season. Maybe a warm shade.//I’m thinking dark purple.
Text.LocalizedString: Next week is already Fall. I might need to change my hair color to match the season. Maybe a warm shade.//I’m thinking dark purple.

Text.SourceString: It doesn’t seem warm enough, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: It doesn’t seem warm enough, huh?

Text.SourceString: I got my dad some bright-yellow rubber boots to wear during Summer, but I think they might be triggering his fashion sense.//<portrait=concerned>He’s used to wearing those clunky, thick boots all year round, poor guy.//<portrait=happy>I guess the obnoxiously yellow color just adds insult to injury.
Text.LocalizedString: I got my dad some bright-yellow rubber boots to wear during Summer, but I think they might be triggering his fashion sense.//<portrait=concerned>He’s used to wearing those clunky, thick boots all year round, poor guy.//<portrait=happy>I guess the obnoxiously yellow color just adds insult to injury.

Text.SourceString: They were the only pair on sale. Who knows, maybe he'll set off a new fashion trend?
Text.LocalizedString: They were the only pair on sale. Who knows, maybe he'll set off a new fashion trend?

Text.SourceString: I was just reading up on this new theory about dark matter.//<portrait=happy>It’s mind-boggling how much we don’t know about the universe. Makes you feel small, doesn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: I was just reading up on this new theory about dark matter.//<portrait=happy>It’s mind-boggling how much we don’t know about the universe. Makes you feel small, doesn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Those free-range osmium-quality eggs taste so much better than the regular ones.//<portrait=normal>Sure, they’re a bit pricier, fifty or sixty coins more per egg. Something like that.//Totally worth it. And mind you, I’m not even a fan of eggs!
Text.LocalizedString: Those free-range osmium-quality eggs taste so much better than the regular ones.//<portrait=normal>Sure, they’re a bit pricier, fifty or sixty coins more per egg. Something like that.//Totally worth it. And mind you, I’m not even a fan of eggs!

Text.SourceString: I’m too lazy to make my own bread.// <NPCName>Sam’s</> is fine.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m too lazy to make my own bread.// <NPCName>Sam’s</> is fine.

Text.SourceString: I got some stuff to decorate the observatory. I don’t mind at all.//The least I can do is take good care of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I got some stuff to decorate the observatory. I don’t mind at all.//The least I can do is take good care of it.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Chaem’s</> always on the move, always at the beach.//And somehow, she still finds time to nab my food.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Chaem’s</> always on the move, always at the beach.//And somehow, she still finds time to nab my food.

Text.SourceString: Nearly became a one-footed astrophysicist yesterday.//<portrait=annoyed>Woke up to find a rogue dumbbell in the kitchen, and let’s just say, my little toe made quite the painful introduction.
Text.LocalizedString: Nearly became a one-footed astrophysicist yesterday.//<portrait=annoyed>Woke up to find a rogue dumbbell in the kitchen, and let’s just say, my little toe made quite the painful introduction.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Takeba</> lives alone, so I sort of keep an eye on him.//He has this habit of lounging outside the bathhouse. I often have to nudge him to go inside when it gets late.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Takeba</> lives alone, so I sort of keep an eye on him.//He has this habit of lounging outside the bathhouse. I often have to nudge him to go inside when it gets late.

Text.SourceString: I spotted one of the cats leaping onto the roof the other day.//Nearly gave me a heart attack.
Text.LocalizedString: I spotted one of the cats leaping onto the roof the other day.//Nearly gave me a heart attack.

Text.SourceString: It was the orange one. That kitty’s got some serious spunk!
Text.LocalizedString: It was the orange one. That kitty’s got some serious spunk!

Text.SourceString: That dog who treats the fountain like his personal swimming pool? Yeah, he’s my neighbor’s.//<portrait=happy>I think <NpcName>Luke</> should consider building him a mini pool. The pup clearly loves water.
Text.LocalizedString: That dog who treats the fountain like his personal swimming pool? Yeah, he’s my neighbor’s.//<portrait=happy>I think <NpcName>Luke</> should consider building him a mini pool. The pup clearly loves water.

Text.SourceString: You know what’s funny? I’ve even seen him out there swimming in Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now, that’s what I call dedication.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what’s funny? I’ve even seen him out there swimming in Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now, that’s what I call dedication.

Text.SourceString: Good thing I keep my hair short, considering the number of times I've dyed it.//<portrait=happy>It's a bit fried, but luckily, it grows out fast.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing I keep my hair short, considering the number of times I've dyed it.//<portrait=happy>It's a bit fried, but luckily, it grows out fast.

Text.SourceString: I'm not big into surfing, but give me a beach to chill on, and I can lose hours.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not big into surfing, but give me a beach to chill on, and I can lose hours.

Text.SourceString: This is my preferred fishing spot.//I’m not a fan of fishing in the creek.
Text.LocalizedString: This is my preferred fishing spot.//I’m not a fan of fishing in the creek.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been working on a new theory about wormholes and their potential for interstellar travel.//<portrait=surprised>It’s like unlocking the secret to the universe’s very own express lane.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been working on a new theory about wormholes and their potential for interstellar travel.//<portrait=surprised>It’s like unlocking the secret to the universe’s very own express lane.

Text.SourceString: Pretty cool, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Pretty cool, huh?

Text.SourceString: I’ve mastered the art of beach bumming.//<portrait=normal>No schedules, no deadlines, just me and a book. Any book. It doesn’t even need to be a good one.//And the endless expanse of the ocean.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve mastered the art of beach bumming.//<portrait=normal>No schedules, no deadlines, just me and a book. Any book. It doesn’t even need to be a good one.//And the endless expanse of the ocean.

Text.SourceString: The clouds look like a giant marshmallow army, plotting a fluffy rebellion against the blue sky.
Text.LocalizedString: The clouds look like a giant marshmallow army, plotting a fluffy rebellion against the blue sky.

Text.SourceString: Pro tip from a beach veteran: Bring your own chair!//<portrait=blushing>Saves you from a case of sun-toasted buns.
Text.LocalizedString: Pro tip from a beach veteran: Bring your own chair!//<portrait=blushing>Saves you from a case of sun-toasted buns.

Text.SourceString: The water feels amazing today.
Text.LocalizedString: The water feels amazing today.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the aroma of freshly brewed coffee and the gentle island breeze.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the aroma of freshly brewed coffee and the gentle island breeze.

Text.SourceString: A customer asked for a decaf espresso the other day, and <NpcName>Raj</>'s face was a mix of confusion and disbelief.//<portrait=annoyed>I can't say I blame them though, that's like asking for a soda without the fizz!
Text.LocalizedString: A customer asked for a decaf espresso the other day, and <NpcName>Raj</>'s face was a mix of confusion and disbelief.//<portrait=annoyed>I can't say I blame them though, that's like asking for a soda without the fizz!

Text.SourceString: If you ever want a sugary coffee concoction with caramel, apple powder, or anything fancy like that, don’t bother asking <NpcName>Raj</>.//<portrait=annoyed>They’re a firm believer in the purity of “real coffee” and won’t hesitate to give you a lecture about it!//I went down that road, trust me. Not worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ever want a sugary coffee concoction with caramel, apple powder, or anything fancy like that, don’t bother asking <NpcName>Raj</>.//<portrait=annoyed>They’re a firm believer in the purity of “real coffee” and won’t hesitate to give you a lecture about it!//I went down that road, trust me. Not worth it.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever tried garlic jam?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever tried garlic jam?

Text.SourceString: Me neither. It sounds pretty gross, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Me neither. It sounds pretty gross, huh?

Special.SourceString: No, not about to try it either.
Special.LocalizedString: No, not about to try it either.

Text.SourceString: You do? What does it taste like?
Text.LocalizedString: You do? What does it taste like?

Text.SourceString: Pets are <Italic>all right</>. They seem like a lot of work, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Pets are <Italic>all right</>. They seem like a lot of work, though.

Text.SourceString: They’re cute and everything, but having a pet is a big commitment, no doubt about it.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re cute and everything, but having a pet is a big commitment, no doubt about it.

Text.SourceString: Last week, I found a four-leaf clover just outside the vineyard.//<portrait=annoyed>Too bad I didn’t have a hoe so I could dig it up and see what was hiding under it.//Missed out on that!
Text.LocalizedString: Last week, I found a four-leaf clover just outside the vineyard.//<portrait=annoyed>Too bad I didn’t have a hoe so I could dig it up and see what was hiding under it.//Missed out on that!

Text.SourceString: I’ve been reading this fascinating book on quantum physics, and it’s mind boggling how our perception of reality can be challenged by the tiniest particles in the universe.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been reading this fascinating book on quantum physics, and it’s mind boggling how our perception of reality can be challenged by the tiniest particles in the universe.

Text.SourceString: I might go for a walk later. I need to clear my mind.
Text.LocalizedString: I might go for a walk later. I need to clear my mind.

Text.SourceString: Wanna watch me work?//<portrait=happy>That sounds so boring. I wouldn’t want to put you through <Italic>that</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Wanna watch me work?//<portrait=happy>That sounds so boring. I wouldn’t want to put you through <Italic>that</>.

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey, stellar!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey, stellar!

Text.SourceString: I’ve been studying the latest advancements in astrophysics, and it’s mind-blowing how our understanding of the universe keeps expanding.//<portrait=normal>The more we discover, the more questions arise.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been studying the latest advancements in astrophysics, and it’s mind-blowing how our understanding of the universe keeps expanding.//<portrait=normal>The more we discover, the more questions arise.

Text.SourceString: It’s amazing!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s amazing!

Text.SourceString: I tried to bake muffins for you. They were going to be my masterpiece. But, um, I failed.//<portrait=sad>The whole batch tasted horrible.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to bake muffins for you. They were going to be my masterpiece. But, um, I failed.//<portrait=sad>The whole batch tasted horrible.

Text.SourceString: They were so bad I decided not to send them your way. I didn’t want to risk offending your taste buds. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: They were so bad I decided not to send them your way. I didn’t want to risk offending your taste buds. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: The night sky up here is clearer than it is at the beach. Perfect for star gazing.//I quite like it.
Text.LocalizedString: The night sky up here is clearer than it is at the beach. Perfect for star gazing.//I quite like it.

Text.SourceString: The night sky here is so clear, perfect for gazing at the stars.//I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: The night sky here is so clear, perfect for gazing at the stars.//I like it.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever notice how cats are always on the roofs here in Starlet Town?//<portrait=surprised>Don’t believe me? I bet you fifty coins the brown cat is on top of <NpcName>Sam’s</> roof right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever notice how cats are always on the roofs here in Starlet Town?//<portrait=surprised>Don’t believe me? I bet you fifty coins the brown cat is on top of <NpcName>Sam’s</> roof right now.

Text.SourceString: I’ve got no clue what I’m eating, honestly. Didn’t order a thing.//<portrait=concerned><NpcName>Jim</> just kinda popped out and handed me this and gave Dad that…<Italic>soup</>?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve got no clue what I’m eating, honestly. Didn’t order a thing.//<portrait=concerned><NpcName>Jim</> just kinda popped out and handed me this and gave Dad that…<Italic>soup</>?

Text.SourceString: It always smells ridiculously good in here.
Text.LocalizedString: It always smells ridiculously good in here.

Text.SourceString: The chairs here are <Italic>so</> colorful.
Text.LocalizedString: The chairs here are <Italic>so</> colorful.

Text.SourceString: And get this, I’m pretty sure I’m sitting in a legit boat. <NpcName>Sunny’s</> all about that thrift-store lifestyle!
Text.LocalizedString: And get this, I’m pretty sure I’m sitting in a legit boat. <NpcName>Sunny’s</> all about that thrift-store lifestyle!

Text.SourceString: I’m spending the weekend with my dad.//We spent the whole morning tackling those pesky weeds in the vegetable patch.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m spending the weekend with my dad.//We spent the whole morning tackling those pesky weeds in the vegetable patch.

Text.SourceString: If I still have any energy after this, I might head out and do a little fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: If I still have any energy after this, I might head out and do a little fishing.

Text.SourceString: Apologies for the dirty hands. What’s up, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Apologies for the dirty hands. What’s up, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: We use this locally sourced fertilizer. Smells kinda funky, but it does the job.
Text.LocalizedString: We use this locally sourced fertilizer. Smells kinda funky, but it does the job.

Text.SourceString: I need to grab some eggs and milk before heading to Dad’s this weekend.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I’ll just do it on the way back.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to grab some eggs and milk before heading to Dad’s this weekend.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I’ll just do it on the way back.

Text.SourceString: Make yourself at home. Sit, sit!
Text.LocalizedString: Make yourself at home. Sit, sit!

Text.SourceString: I like your hair. Did you do something new to it?
Text.LocalizedString: I like your hair. Did you do something new to it?

Text.SourceString: Is it stuffy in here? I can open some windows if you want.
Text.LocalizedString: Is it stuffy in here? I can open some windows if you want.

Text.SourceString: Now that I think about it, I don’t want bugs coming in. Sorry!//<portrait=normal>But I agree it does get stuffy in here.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that I think about it, I don’t want bugs coming in. Sorry!//<portrait=normal>But I agree it does get stuffy in here.

Special.SourceString: It’s stuffy, yeah. I could use some air.
Special.LocalizedString: It’s stuffy, yeah. I could use some air.

Text.SourceString: Are you sure? Okay.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want bugs coming in. It’s hard to get rid of them once they’re inside.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you sure? Okay.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want bugs coming in. It’s hard to get rid of them once they’re inside.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Raj</> is always going on about wanting to put flowers in their beard, but I’ve yet to see them actually do it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Raj</> is always going on about wanting to put flowers in their beard, but I’ve yet to see them actually do it.

Text.SourceString: If you’re planning to eat your muffin here, keep an eye on it.//The seagulls around this place are cheeky, and they’ll snatch it in a heartbeat.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re planning to eat your muffin here, keep an eye on it.//The seagulls around this place are cheeky, and they’ll snatch it in a heartbeat.

Text.SourceString: I prefer reading in the observatory because there are way too many distractions here.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s hard to concentrate.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer reading in the observatory because there are way too many distractions here.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s hard to concentrate.

Text.SourceString: Conferences aren’t really my thing, but they do have their perks.
Text.LocalizedString: Conferences aren’t really my thing, but they do have their perks.

Text.SourceString: Oh! I happened to sit next to Stellar Hawkings once at a conference in Pokyo.//<portrait=happy>It was the only empty seat, but <Italic>dang</>, that was a lucky break! Got to chat with him and everything!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I happened to sit next to Stellar Hawkings once at a conference in Pokyo.//<portrait=happy>It was the only empty seat, but <Italic>dang</>, that was a lucky break! Got to chat with him and everything!

Text.SourceString: Are you cold? Want my jacket?//<portrait=happy>Make sure you don’t stay out too late today, all right?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you cold? Want my jacket?//<portrait=happy>Make sure you don’t stay out too late today, all right?

Text.SourceString: I don’t want you to get sick.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want you to get sick.

Text.SourceString: This Winter, Dad and I are planting some tea. He bought the seeds from <NpcName>Ben</>.//<portrait=annoyed>They’re, like, from some island or something.
Text.LocalizedString: This Winter, Dad and I are planting some tea. He bought the seeds from <NpcName>Ben</>.//<portrait=annoyed>They’re, like, from some island or something.

Text.SourceString: Having a pool table at home might be fun!
Text.LocalizedString: Having a pool table at home might be fun!

Text.SourceString: Ah, let’s face it, it wouldn’t be as enjoyable. Who am I kidding?!//<portrait=happy>Half of the fun is playing right here.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, let’s face it, it wouldn’t be as enjoyable. Who am I kidding?!//<portrait=happy>Half of the fun is playing right here.

Text.SourceString: I think <NpcName>Pablo’s</> my toughest competitor when it comes to pool.
Text.LocalizedString: I think <NpcName>Pablo’s</> my toughest competitor when it comes to pool.

Text.SourceString: I don’t always come here for a drink. Sometimes it’s nice to just chill or play pool.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t always come here for a drink. Sometimes it’s nice to just chill or play pool.

Text.SourceString: By the way, I have a running tab at the bar. Feel free to put your order on it, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=normal>Just let <NpcName>Frank</> know.
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, I have a running tab at the bar. Feel free to put your order on it, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=normal>Just let <NpcName>Frank</> know.

Text.SourceString: Who’s up for a game of darts? Loser buys the next round of drinks!
Text.LocalizedString: Who’s up for a game of darts? Loser buys the next round of drinks!

Text.SourceString: After I’m done with this, though.//Finishing up a round here.
Text.LocalizedString: After I’m done with this, though.//Finishing up a round here.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been told the cake here is amazing, especially the red velvet.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been told the cake here is amazing, especially the red velvet.

Text.SourceString: You could say I have a sweet tooth. I enjoy treats like cenil and muffins.//But I also like other stuff, like mangoes…and, oh gosh, tacos.
Text.LocalizedString: You could say I have a sweet tooth. I enjoy treats like cenil and muffins.//But I also like other stuff, like mangoes…and, oh gosh, tacos.

Text.SourceString: The vegan ones, though. Vegan tacos are the <Italic>superior</> ones! Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: The vegan ones, though. Vegan tacos are the <Italic>superior</> ones! Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: My dad thinks you’re a great farmer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//He has a lot of respect for you.
Text.LocalizedString: My dad thinks you’re a great farmer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//He has a lot of respect for you.

Text.SourceString: I obviously think so too.
Text.LocalizedString: I obviously think so too.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, it won’t rain this weekend.//Kinda in the mood for fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, it won’t rain this weekend.//Kinda in the mood for fishing.

Text.SourceString: I’ve noticed a fair number of people coming in and out of the bathhouse today.//They’re likely popping by to check on <NpcName>Takeba</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve noticed a fair number of people coming in and out of the bathhouse today.//They’re likely popping by to check on <NpcName>Takeba</>.

Text.SourceString: Keeping busy with the hot spring seems to be good for <NpcName>Takeba</>.//<portrait=happy>I think he enjoys looking after it.//<portrait=normal>Gives him a sense of purpose, something to do.
Text.LocalizedString: Keeping busy with the hot spring seems to be good for <NpcName>Takeba</>.//<portrait=happy>I think he enjoys looking after it.//<portrait=normal>Gives him a sense of purpose, something to do.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Takeba’s</> memory is spotty. He lost his son in a war, but he often forgets that.//<portrait=sad>It makes me worry about Dad. I hope it doesn’t ever get to that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Takeba’s</> memory is spotty. He lost his son in a war, but he often forgets that.//<portrait=sad>It makes me worry about Dad. I hope it doesn’t ever get to that.

Text.SourceString: And if it ever does happen and I’m not here, I hope the people in this town take care of him like they do <NpcName>Takeba</>.
Text.LocalizedString: And if it ever does happen and I’m not here, I hope the people in this town take care of him like they do <NpcName>Takeba</>.

Text.SourceString: Don’t slip going down the stairs!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t slip going down the stairs!

Text.SourceString: I have nothing against Mayor <NpcName> Connor</>, but sometimes I wish we could have a younger person in charge.//<portrait=normal>Give the next generation a chance to lead, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I have nothing against Mayor <NpcName> Connor</>, but sometimes I wish we could have a younger person in charge.//<portrait=normal>Give the next generation a chance to lead, right?

Text.SourceString: Who knows, we might even get to see some modern innovations around here.
Text.LocalizedString: Who knows, we might even get to see some modern innovations around here.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad Starlet Town decided against constructing that tourist podium.//Can you imagine the throngs of people? It would seriously be hard to get anything productive done.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad Starlet Town decided against constructing that tourist podium.//Can you imagine the throngs of people? It would seriously be hard to get anything productive done.

Text.SourceString: I could hang out here for hours. I just need to keep a watchful eye on the cat.//Don’t want it to end up scratching you.
Text.LocalizedString: I could hang out here for hours. I just need to keep a watchful eye on the cat.//Don’t want it to end up scratching you.

Text.SourceString: If you had to choose, who would you elect as mayor?
Text.LocalizedString: If you had to choose, who would you elect as mayor?

Text.SourceString: Yes, same here. I’d vote for <NpcName>Millie</> too.//I think she’d make a great mayor. She knows this town inside and out.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, same here. I’d vote for <NpcName>Millie</> too.//I think she’d make a great mayor. She knows this town inside and out.

Text.SourceString: Interesting choice.//He seems a bit too chill to be a mayor, but that’s just my opinion.//<portrait=happy>He’d make an <Italic>interesting</> mayor, I’ll admit.
Text.LocalizedString: Interesting choice.//He seems a bit too chill to be a mayor, but that’s just my opinion.//<portrait=happy>He’d make an <Italic>interesting</> mayor, I’ll admit.

Text.SourceString: Me? Wow! Thank you. I’m really flattered.//<portrait=normal>But I don’t think I’d make a good mayor.//<NpcName>Millie</> might. Or <NpcName>Sam</>.//They both seem wise.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? Wow! Thank you. I’m really flattered.//<portrait=normal>But I don’t think I’d make a good mayor.//<NpcName>Millie</> might. Or <NpcName>Sam</>.//They both seem wise.
